# Vault Overview

This is an Obsidian second brain managed primarily through Cursor (AI agent). The user captures notes by talking to the agent. The agent organizes, extracts tasks, and maintains the vault.

## Folder Structure

| Folder | Purpose |
| --- | --- |
| `Quick Capture/` | Temporary landing zone. Notes arrive here first, get processed on organize. |
| `Daily Notes/` | One note per day (`YYYY-MM-DD.md`). Quick captures and tasks default here. |
| `Personal/` | Personal life вҖ” long-running tasks, standalone notes, ideas. |
| `Work/` | Work вҖ” long-running tasks, standalone notes, projects. |
| `Archive/` | Processed captures, completed items, old notes. |
| `Templates/` | Note, Project, Daily, Task templates. |
| `.cursor/Skills/` | Agent instructions for Organize and Review workflows. |
| `.cursor/Prompts/` | Saved reusable AI prompts. |
| `.cursor/rules/` | Agent rules (this file and command shortcuts). |

Assets and resources should not live in the vault root. Put project-specific files in an `assets/` folder inside the project folder, e.g. `Work/ILS/assets/`. Use a top-level `Assets/` folder only for shared or unclassified resources.

## Shortcuts

| User types | Agent does |
| --- | --- |
| `qqq <text>` | Create a note in `Quick Capture/` вҖ” capture only, don't organize. |
| `ooo` | Organize: process all `Quick Capture/` notes into daily notes, extract tasks. |
| `review` | Vault health check вҖ” count notes, list open tasks, flag stale items. |

## Task format

Tasks use the **Tasks plugin emoji format** inside markdown checkboxes:

```
- [ ] Task description рҹ“… 2026-02-24
- [ ] Urgent task вҸ« рҹ“… 2026-02-24
- [x] Done task вң… 2026-02-23
```

Emoji: `рҹ“…` due, `вҸі` scheduled, `рҹӣ«` start, `вҸ«` high priority, `рҹ”ј` medium, `рҹ”Ҫ` low, `вң…` done.

## Key rules

1. **Capture and organize are separate steps.** `qqq` only captures. `ooo` organizes.
2. **Daily note is the default destination.** Quick tasks and captures go to `Daily Notes/YYYY-MM-DD.md` unless the user says otherwise.
3. **Standalone notes only when needed.** Long-running working items get their own note in `Personal/` or `Work/`. Everything else stays in the daily note.
4. **Append, never overwrite.** Daily notes accumulate throughout the day.
5. **Use shallow project folders when useful.** Larger projects may live under one extra level, e.g. `Work/ILS/` or `Work/RDR/`. Honor existing project folders when organizing.
6. **Organize assets with their context.** Images, PDFs, and other resources go beside the note/project they support, usually in a project `assets/` folder.
7. **Don't over-organize.** Keep it simple вҖ” Personal or Work first, then only one shallow project folder for substantial projects. Don't invent categories for one-off notes.
8. **Tasks plugin powers TODO views.** `TODOs - Personal.md` and `TODOs - Work.md` use `tasks` query blocks to show individual checkboxes across the vault.
